# stack-supabase — managed Supabase

## What it is

Open-source Firebase alternative on Postgres. Auth, RLS, Realtime, Storage, Edge Functions, Storage.

## When I choose it

v0/v1 of solo-dev mobile-first products. See adr-0001-tech-stack-flutter-and-supabase.

## When I avoid it

Apps that need >1000 DAU on a tight budget (cost jumps). Then migrate per adr-0002-backend-self-host-strategy.

## Conventions I follow

- RLS enabled on every table. No exceptions.
- Service-role key NEVER in client — anon key only.
- All access through a Repository — see adr-0008-data-access-repository-pattern-for-portability.
- Secrets via --dart-define or flutter_dotenv.
- Auth state via supabase.auth.onAuthStateChange.
- Server-side validation in RPCs (SQL functions), never trust the client.

## Common gotchas

- Realtime channel subscriptions leak — dispose in Notifier.onDispose.
- RLS: `auth.uid()` is null for anon, fail closed.
- Storage URLs expire — sign on the server, not the client, for private buckets.

